		<div class="about-us__heading">
			<h1 class="section-headers__title">About Us</h1>
			<img src="/assets/images/about-us/header-pic-600w-smaller.jpg">
			<p class="section-headers__line-highlight">
				<strong>Who are we and what qualifies us</strong> to give you tips on how you should plan your trip?
			</p>
			<p> 
				First of all, <strong>we had never travelled before</strong>  – at least not like this. We went into this trip with a general knowledge of our budget, timeframe and what we wanted to do, but that was it. There were many things that we learned along the way but <strong>we wished we had a website that could have guided us better</strong> through our journey. We’re hoping to give you the opportunity to learn from our mistakes instead of having to make them, as well as hearing about the things we did right.
			</p>
			<p>
				From Guelph Ontario, Canada, we are a couple in our mid twenties who both graduated in 2016 and wanted to take a trip before stepping into the “real world”. We have been together upwards of five years now and, although it’s tough to travel with anyone, we had a stellar time on our trip. Totalling a whopping <strong>twelve feet, six inches</strong> we never lost each other. 
			</p>
			<p>
				We chose South America because of its <strong>natural beauty, abundance of adventure, and it’s budget friendly to boot!</strong> At first, we were a bit scared because when you hear about South America you may think of crime and poverty. We aren’t going to pretend that it’s completely safe, but we wouldn’t say we ever felt like it was more dangerous than walking in the wrong part of Toronto late at night. The more we researched, the more we realized that you have to be conscious and safe (as with travelling anywhere foreign to you) and yes, even so you may get mugged, but that’s absolutely no reason to avoid a place as beautiful as South America. 
			</p>
			<p class="section-headers__line-highlight">
				<strong>Our goal with this website</strong> is to give you a good base for your trip, but not to live it for you.
			</p>
			<p>
				Some of the most frustrating things that happened on our trip were very well-meaning people telling us everything there was to know about the city/tour that we were going to next. When they did this, it made our expectations high and there was little surprise and wonder left. We want to make sure you <strong>don’t miss out on anything</strong> big or small but we are not here to explain every little detail – those details are yours to discover.
			</p>	
		</div>

		
		<div class="two-column-flex two-column-flex__less-margin-b">
