			<div class="two-column-flex__description">
				<h2 class="section-headers__subheading section-headers--no-margin">Thomas</h2>
				<p>
					Hi! I’m Thomas. Let me tell you some stuff. My most distinguishing feature would be my height; I’m 6’ 6’. From trying to fit through doors to constantly being pointed at, there were times that I felt like I was the world wonder! 

				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>I was incredibly nervous to travel</strong> through South America. I’ve never really travelled before and I didn’t know what to expect but in the end I’m SO glad I did it and can’t wait to start planning our next adventure!
				</p>
				<p class="section-headers__bold-line">
					Backpacking was more than climbing mountains and exploring places I’ve never seen before. Of course these experiences were beyond amazing but it’s the culture and way of life that really had an impact on me. 
					Despite the disadvantages these people face for living in third world countries, they were some of the happiest and kindest people I have ever met. Being submerged in the culture made me examine what’s really important in my own life and the little things that I was taking for granted. 

				</p>
			</div>	
		</div>
		<div>
			<p class="section-headers__line-highlight">
				In the end people remember stories, not numbers.
			</p>
			<p>
				When we got back from our trip I wanted to take all of our adventures and and share them with people to help maximize their experience as well as create a cool way to preserve our memories. However, because I’m weird and love to learn new things, I decided to teach myself web development and create this website from scratch so we could deliver a unique product that we were proud of. This also explains why this website has taken a little while to come into fruition. 
			</p>
			<p>
				You can also check out my personal blog where I have posts about my journey of learning to code from scratch, any random thoughts I have, as well as my next super secret project that is in the works….
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="two-column-flex">
			<div class="two-column-flex__description">
				<h2 class="section-headers__subheading section-headers--no-margin">Reilly</h2>
				<p>
					Born in 1990, the youngest of 4 children (and the only girl), I’ve grown up with a sense of adventure. Travelling has always been something I wanted to do, but <strong>I never realized the impact it would have on me.</strong> I also didn’t know a damn thing I was doing when we got there. Fumbling through the first few weeks was one of the most challenging experiences of my life. 
				</p>
				<p>
					There are so many things that I would do differently if I had the chance, but at the same time, the experience was an unbelievable one that I wouldn’t trade for the world. Well, maybe I would trade the first few days where the altitude got the better of me...
				</p>
				<p>
					When I say travelling impacted my life, I believe the places you visit will impact you in all different ways. The amazing thing about South America is that you get a little taste of everything. We visited towns that didn’t have running water and no one spoke a lick of English, and we went to cities that were so vibrant and built-up you’d think you were back in North America – but better. 
				</p>
				<p>
					Each place will have a distinct and lasting impression on you.  For me, it was a mix of the landscape and the people that left the impression. From the breathtaking mountains of Bolivia, to the kindest people I’ve ever met in Colombia, <strong>every step of our journey is something I will always remember.</strong>
				</p>
